    "MOA_summary": "Dr. Lattai outlined the NCI's funding landscape, highlighting a 34% decline in US cancer death rates since 1991, a $128\u202fM budget increase to $7.3\u202fB for FY2026, and a shift to multi\u2011year and Select Pay funding mechanisms that maintain scientific merit while providing flexibility. He emphasized new priorities such as functional precision medicine, cancer vaccine trials, prevention and screening initiatives, and efforts to accelerate clinical trial activation.",
    "readouts": [],
    "key_findings": [
      "US cancer death rates have fallen 34% since 1991, reflecting improved screening, prevention, and therapies.",
      "NCI FY2026 budget increased by $128\u202fM to a total of $7.3\u202fB, representing a record level of extramural funding.",
      "Approximately 200 new competing and 1,500 non\u2011competing extramural grants have been processed for FY2026.",
      "Projected R01 success rate for FY2026 is ~11%, with a target of ~120 Early Stage Investigator awards.",
      "NCI will fund three new therapeutic cancer vaccine trials over the next three years through a public\u2011private partnership with FNIH."
